Description: Bust to right, laureate. Wears paludamentum and cuirass. (obverse)
Athena standing to left, wears helmet and chiton with diplois. Holds little Nike right bearing wreath and palm, and places hand on shield which rests on ground. (reverse)
Bibliographic references: BMC Greek (Alexandria) / Catalogue of the coins of Alexandria and the Nomes (2483, p.322)
Errington 1999 / Rediscovering the Collections of Charles Masson (p.227, pl.6.24)
